<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedqvist" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Proteaceae" genus="Dinapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dinapsis oculohirta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculohirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dinapsis oculohirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from southern Madagascar (Anosy and Toliara [= Tulear] provinces). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedqvist" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Proteaceae" genus="Dinapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dinapsis oculohirta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculohirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dinapsis oculohirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was named for the conspicuous dense setae that cover the compound eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Dinapsis oculohirta holotype female (MNHN) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C head, mesosoma, dorsal view D head, mesosoma, lateral view E head, anterior view F wings, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1000 µm (A, B); 500 µm (C, D, F); 200 µm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.82307.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/714035" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">19C, E</figureCitation>
). It can be distinguished from other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedqvist" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Proteaceae" genus="Dinapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dinapsis oculohirta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculohirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dinapsis oculohirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by the presence of a small median groove between the ocelli (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Dinapsis oculohirta holotype female (MNHN) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C head, mesosoma, dorsal view D head, mesosoma, lateral view E head, anterior view F wings, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1000 µm (A, B); 500 µm (C, D, F); 200 µm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.82307.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/714035" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">19E</figureCitation>
). See also couplet 6 of the key to species, and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedqvist" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Proteaceae" genus="Dinapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dinapsis oculohirta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculohirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dinapsis oculohirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group discussion in the species-group section of this paper.
</paragraph>
